    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds like something people say just to feel better about the void. it's just a coping mechanism, isn't it? pretending there's \"beauty\" because the alternative—that it's all just cold, indifferent physics—is too terrifying to face. it doesn't change the fact that nothing actually matters.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
